<subSubSection pageNumber="314" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="314">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="314">Note:</emphasis>
Hitchcock (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="314">Contr. U. S. Natl. Herb.</emphasis>
12: 123. 1908) designated a Browne specimen at LINN as type but did not specify which of the two Browne specimens he intended. Griffiths (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="314">Contr. U. S. Natl. Herb.</emphasis>
14: 407. 1912) made a similar statement while Judziewicz (in 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Görts-van">Goerts-van</normalizedToken>
Rijn, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="314">Fl. Guianas</emphasis>
, ser. A, 8: 50. 1990) indicated 98.2 and 98.3 (LINN) as syntypes. None of these statements is an effective typification in its own right, so sheet 98.2 (LINN) was formally chosen as 
<typeStatus>lectotype</typeStatus>
by Davidse, a restriction of 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Hitchcock’s">Hitchcock's</normalizedToken>
original choice under Art. 9.15 of the Code.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
